recalls.Component: SERVICE BRAKES, HYDRAULIC:ANTILOCK/TRACTION CONTROL/ELECTRONIC LIMITED SLIP:CONTROL UNIT/MODULE
recalls.Summary: McLaren Automotive Incorporated (McClaren) is recalling certain 2020-2025 600LT, 720S, Artura, GT, and GTS vehicles.  The brake lines may be routed incorrectly and cause the brakes on the incorrect side to activate, possibly resulting in one of the rear wheels locking up.
recalls.Consequence: A rear wheel locking condition may cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and correct the brake line connections as necessary, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on April 21, 2025.  Owners may contact McClaren customer service at 1-646-429-8916.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1- 888-275-9171) or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

issues.title: High Voltage Battery Pack Failure
issues.description: Complete failure of the high voltage battery pack causing the vehicle to become inoperable. The hybrid system fails to engage and the vehicle cannot start or run in electric mode.
issues.fix_description: Complete battery pack replacement at McLaren service center
issues.prevention: Follow proper charging procedures and avoid deep discharge cycles

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Crashes
issues.description: The McLaren Infotainment System (MIS) frequently freezes, crashes, or becomes unresponsive, affecting climate control, navigation, and vehicle settings.
issues.fix_description: Software update or complete infotainment unit replacement
issues.prevention: Avoid rapid input commands and ensure software is up to date

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: Electronic door handles fail to operate properly, preventing entry or exit from the vehicle. The mechanism becomes stuck or unresponsive.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle assembly and actuator mechanism
issues.prevention: Regular operation and avoiding force when handles don't respond

issues.title: Charging Port Malfunction
issues.description: The charging port fails to open, close, or properly connect to charging equipment, preventing the hybrid battery from being charged.
issues.fix_description: Replace charging port assembly and related wiring
issues.prevention: Keep charging port clean and avoid forcing connections

issues.title: Active Suspension System Faults
issues.description: The adaptive dampers and active suspension system experience failures, causing harsh ride quality and handling issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty dampers and suspension control modules
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme driving conditions and maintain proper tire pressures

issues.title: Coolant System Leaks
issues.description: Multiple coolant leaks from various points in the complex cooling system serving both the engine and hybrid components.
issues.fix_description: Identify and replace leaking hoses, gaskets, or pump components
issues.prevention: Regular coolant level checks and scheduled maintenance

issues.title: Brake System Warning Lights
issues.description: False brake system warnings appear on the dashboard despite properly functioning brakes, often related to brake fluid sensors.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake fluid level sensor or update brake control module software
issues.prevention: Regular brake system maintenance and fluid checks

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Body Panel Delamination
issues.description: Carbon fiber body panels show signs of delamination or clear coat failure, particularly around high-heat areas.
issues.fix_description: Panel refinishing or complete panel replacement
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperatures and use proper car care products

issues.title: Tire Pressure Monitoring System Errors
issues.description: TPMS sensors provide inaccurate readings or fail to communicate with the vehicle's monitoring system.
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty TPMS sensors and recalibrate system
issues.prevention: Regular tire maintenance and avoiding tire mounting damage

issues.title: Engine Cover Fitment Issues
issues.description: Poor fitment of engine bay covers and panels, causing rattling noises and potential damage to components.
issues.fix_description: Readjust panel alignment and replace worn mounting hardware
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of panel fitment during service

editorial.tagline: McLaren's hybrid revolution meets supercar perfection
editorial.hero_blurb: The Artura represents McLaren's bold leap into electrified performance, delivering 671 horsepower from its revolutionary twin-turbo V6 hybrid powertrain. This isn't just evolution—it's a complete reimagining of what a McLaren can be.
editorial.essence: The Artura pioneers McLaren's new era with a lightweight carbon fiber architecture and sophisticated hybrid system that enhances rather than compromises the driving experience. It's the first McLaren designed from the ground up around electrification, creating a more refined yet equally thrilling supercar.
editorial.heritage: Launched in 2022 as McLaren's first series-production hybrid supercar, the Artura sits between the 570S and 720S in the lineup while introducing the all-new McLaren Carbon Lightweight Architecture (MCLA). It marks McLaren's transition from pure combustion engines to electrified performance.
editorial.design_philosophy: McLaren's designers crafted the Artura around the principle of 'everything for a reason,' with each surface serving aerodynamic or cooling purposes. The shrink-wrapped bodywork follows function over flash, creating a purposeful aesthetic that's unmistakably McLaren yet distinctly modern.
editorial.motorsport_history: While the Artura itself is new to competition, it carries McLaren's Formula 1 DNA through advanced aerodynamics, carbon fiber construction, and hybrid technology lessons learned from the championship-winning MCL35M race car.
editorial.engine_character: The 3.0-liter twin-turbo V6 hybrid delivers instant torque from the electric motor while the combustion engine builds to a crescendo, creating a seamless power delivery that's both brutal and refined. The electric assist eliminates traditional turbo lag completely.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 8-speed dual-clutch transmission shifts with lightning precision, offering knife-edge quick changes in Track mode while remaining smooth and refined in Comfort. Manual mode provides satisfying paddle control with perfect rev-matching.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The carbon fiber monocoque provides incredible rigidity while adaptive dampers and anti-roll bars create a chassis that's both compliant over rough roads and razor-sharp on track. The weight distribution benefits from the battery's low placement.
editorial.steering_feel: Electro-hydraulic steering delivers pure, unfiltered feedback with perfectly weighted resistance that builds naturally with cornering forces. The connection to the front wheels feels direct and confidence-inspiring at any speed.
editorial.brake_confidence: Carbon ceramic brakes provide tremendous stopping power with excellent modulation and fade resistance. The brake-by-wire system seamlessly blends regenerative and friction braking for consistent pedal feel.
editorial.sound_signature: The V6 produces a distinctive high-pitched wail that's uniquely McLaren—less rumbling bass than a V8 but with an intoxicating metallic edge that builds to an addictive crescendo. The hybrid system adds an otherworldly electric whir during low-speed operation.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving enthusiasts who want cutting-edge hybrid technology without sacrificing the pure McLaren experience, and those who appreciate being early adopters of automotive innovation while still demanding track-day capability.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Traditionalists who prefer naturally aspirated engines, buyers seeking maximum luggage space, or those who prioritize brand prestige over technological advancement.
editorial.buyers_summary: The Artura represents McLaren's most sophisticated offering yet, combining hybrid efficiency with uncompromised performance. While early production had some teething issues, the 2023+ models offer improved reliability and remain the most accessible way into hybrid supercar ownership.

LIGHTING: Golden hour sunlight streaming through large industrial windows. Warm color temperature. Cinematic depth.
